## Review System

Code is reviewed automatically via hooks at two stages:

- **Per-edit**: `readonly-guard.sh` blocks writes to protected files
- **Pre-commit**: `commit-review-gate.sh` — headless Claude Sonnet reviews the full staged diff before commit
- **Post-edit**: `auto-format.sh` — auto-runs project formatter after every edit
- **Safety**: `safety-net.sh` — blocks destructive commands (`rm -rf`, `git push --force`, etc.)
- **On stop**: `test-gate.sh` — runs the test suite before Claude finishes a task
- **Alternative review**: `/qwen-review` skill — local Qwen2.5-Coder via Ollama (airgapped)
- **Legacy per-edit review**: `sonnet-review-gate.sh` available but not active by default

## Context Management

IMPORTANT: When compacting, always preserve the full list of modified files, the current
subtask being worked on, and any test commands or error output from the most recent run.

